race.comment: EXTOL (2) spiked his figures placing here at the trip and then came back and found one much too good. He was backed off the map in that, and on a quick back-up is capable of making amends. BATTLESPACE (7) has been threatening another win and will find this easier than Ipswich last time. Enjoys the mile and deserves another chance. SOMETHING FORJO (6) didn't manage the step up in distance at Kilcoy in stronger, but most of his recent form at this distance reads well. Has a low gate and handy 2kg claim and will get every chance in a suitable assignment. LONDON POINT (4) will be fitter and should be around the mark.
